<h3> 3 Equations 3 Unknowns Solver </h3>
Let <b>x</b>, <b>y</b>, and <b>z</b> be variables and a, b, y, j, d, e, f, k, g, h, i, and m be constants.<br>
The the unique solution <b>x</b> = x0, <b>y</b> = y0, and <b>z</b> = z0 that satisfies the 3 equations<br>
a<b>x</b> + by + cz = j<br>
dx + ey + fz = k<br>
gx + hy + iz = m<br>
is the point in which these 3 planes intersect.<br>
